# GCE VECTREX · GCE VECTREX · exereunesis · teardown · 1982 · UD0 / exereunesis

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of GCE VECTREX](the-vectrex.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (GCE VECTREX's organic-form embodiment): the-vectrex.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** GCE VECTREX — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** Unique among consoles, the Vectrex came with its own built-in vector monitor — it drew crisp glowing lines directly, not a grid of pixels, so it never needed a TV. A Motorola 6809 steered the beam through a DAC, and plastic overlays added colour to the black-and-white screen.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Unique among consoles, the Vectrex came with its own built-in vector monitor — it drew crisp glowing lines directly, not a grid of pixels, so it never needed a TV. A Motorola 6809 steered the beam through a DAC, and plastic overlays added colour to the black-and-white screen.

